    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chive-crumbed-basa-with-veg-and-lemony-mayo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped chives</strong> with your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and stir it together until all of the breadcrumbs are coated in the oil \u2013 this is your <strong>chive crumb</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chive-crumbed-basa-with-veg-and-lemony-mayo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) and pat dry with kitchen<strong> </strong>paper</p><p>Top the fish evenly with the <strong>chive crumb</strong> and press it into the fish using the back of a spoon</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden and cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>breaded fish</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chive-crumbed-basa-with-veg-and-lemony-mayo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, combine a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong> with your <strong>mayo</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>lemony mayo</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chive-crumbed-basa-with-veg-and-lemony-mayo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into batons</p><p>Add the <strong>carrot batons</strong> to a pot with a lid, with plenty of <strong>boiling water</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 3 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chive-crumbed-basa-with-veg-and-lemony-mayo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>peas </strong>and cook for 2 min further or until everything's tender</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>vegetables</strong> and return them to the pot with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chive-crumbed-basa-with-veg-and-lemony-mayo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chive-crumbed-basa-with-veg-and-lemony-mayo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>breaded fish</strong> with the <strong>vegetables</strong> and <strong>lemony mayo</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge </strong>and enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
